caption: Great service and the best onion rings I've ever had.
Our server was great! Genuine and good with recommendations. They have a pumpkin sour that almost made me consider becoming a "basic girl". If your in Philly you have to stop by!!
King of barrel aged beers here in Philly.  All the sours are worthy of appreciation.  Nice people working there as well.  Food is on point too.

This is great place to go have a few drinks here in Philly. The space is very big and they have events here a lot some of which are pretty cool. Their beer is pretty good on top of it. Definitely a place to go a check out.

Great spot!  A variety of options for food and drink. Our bartender was very helpful. She clearly explained the selections of beers/ cocktails- and recommended  delicious snacks/ dinner. Do not miss out on this place!!  Looking forward to a return visit.
Fantastic as always. So nice to be allowed to dine inside again.

Horrible service. Attitude from the bartender. Won’t be back.
Whoever was cooking the pizza tonight was great! Easily one of the best pizzas I had in my area yet. That you for the delicious food!

Best sour beer and NE IPAs in philly hands down!  Friendly and helpful brewers too :)

The beers are decent here, kind of a mixed bag, but the sours are great.  The sours are like a dollar extra and totally worth it.  The atmosphere here is really good, and the service is great.  The menu is fantastic, and some of the best grilled octopus I've ever had!
The food and drinks were incredibly good. Every employee here was kind and this place had a very welcoming environment.

My friend and I came in hating sour beers but due to most of what was on tap we didn't have much of a choice. We walked out of there wishing to get our hands on some more soon. Also the food was pretty on point when I wanted to order seconds.
Nice place out side of china town.
Great food, service and beer. Awesome place for a quick drink or a full dinner.
Great beer and a small selection of board games as well!!
Excellent Place to eat with a nice beer selection and nice Atmosphere.
Best of Philly!  - Amazing food, great beer, perfect atmosphere! Great for events as well.

Good atmosphere, great service BUT the pizza was one of the saltiest dinners I've ever gotten at a restaurant- why the need for so much salt? Hopefully, this was a fluke but I'm not going to take the chance of wasting $17 on a barely edible dinner again.
Excellent bar service with great tasting beers
Very friendly and helpful staff. Great beer and food! I will definitely go there again next time I am in Philly!
Excellent bar with great happy hour deals. Good beer selection on draft and a great atmosphere to boot. Bartenders were very friendly and provided great service.

First stop on our mini beer tour, primarily since it is one of the breweries open on a Thursday for lunch.  We were pleasantly surprised at the quality of the beer and food and enjoyed our lunch.  The loaded fries were awesome.

Great place for an event. Hosted a corporate happy hour here and the staff was incredibly helpful and provided great service. The online booking tool made the planning process simple and easy and I knew the exact cost which made operating within a budget a breeze. Thanks guys!

Knowledgable and friendly staff, quick service, neat place inside and out, street parking only. Many sour beers offered, which I personally don't like but others really enjoyed. I liked the Daddy Fat Sacks IPA. $3 pints during happy hour.

Great beer, great food. Bad lighting. It's like target bright white florescent lighting so this may not be your romantic date spot but aside from that I love this place.

We had a baby shower here for about 25 people and couldn't be happier. The food and drinks were great, top notch service and all guests had a great time. Parking was not an issue at all. We had the liquid art corner space and were able to decorate. Mike and staff ensured we had everything we needed. We highly recommend it.

Live bands and good beer. Surprisingly large sour selection. $3 Happy Hour beers, many to pick. The unusually low urinals in the mens room might coincide with the presence of children during the evening hours, either that or they had a short plumber.
Great beer and tasty food. Loved the soft pretzels! Will look forward to coming back and trying the rest of the draft list.

The food is amazing. The beer less so. For a brewery Id hoped to have better beer. Between the twelve beers we tried with my party we struggled to find one we'd order again. Especially at the price we paid.
Loved the food and the sour beers.
Barrel House has a welcoming and friendly atmosphere, a broad and affordable beer list, and friendly, knowledgeable staff. Tom, my bartender, knows his stuff and generously made suggestions.
Unique place, good food and reasonable prices with friendly service.

Cool spot on Spring Garden st in philly. Good craft beer selection made in house or there Brewing Co in Chamersburg, Pa. Great Food selection from Fried Brussels to Chicken Schnitzel & other very tasty foods! Highly Recommend... Tasty food & Liquid Art! Roy Pitz Barrel House is 5 star in my book. EXCELLENT. A variety of beer worth appreciating. A happy hour special to die for and service that makes you feel warm and welcomed. I had their Coffee Rubbed Beer Braised Short Rib and was floored by the taste, quality and presentation. Make this somewhere you visit soon!

Truly honest ale is top notch. Great menu, great beer, awesome bartenders. LSD Habanero is the perfect amount of spicy on a wing. I always think the bathroom is a good judge of a bar and this place is dope.
Had a blast! Amazing and (very) patient staff!! Tasty dranks as well. Great evening and very friendly atmosphere

This brewery is huge and fantastic for groups!!! So many draft selections to choose from and they have unique flavours. I also had the pretzel and beer cheese which was delicious. The staff are great at their jobs and they go above and beyond. Also they have some cool art on display to checkout !
Good beer

Good selection of beers in a much larger venue than their Chambersburg location. The beer was good as well as the food, we especially enjoyed the charcuterie board with a great mix of meats and cheeses.
Good location.
Friendly bartender. Lovely tasting beer. Ila was great! The taster flights were excellent. Artwork and glasswork was great! Would visit again. Did not yet try the food but it smelled delicious.

Great beer destination in Philly. Came with a large group of friends, plenty of room for all of us. Staff was friendly and knowledgeable about their beer and the area. The bar is huge and the place has a  cool industrial feel. Will definitely stop in next time I'm in town.
Decent but not stellar
A cavernous and empty space for lunch on Wednesday afternoon. But the beer choice is wide and the pilsner is tasty. Very fine burger, too.
Good beer great service and food

good brew but place gets kinds loud even when half empty.
I liked the beers that I tried and the cubano was pretty good.

Came here for Happy Hour before Paint Nite and am so glad I found this place! Wide and spacious with long picnic tables and benches as well as individual dining tables in a casual industrial vibe. Comfortable and attentive service. Delicious burgers and great beers on tap! Will definitely be returning.
Great sours and great food!
Really good food!
Looks like a sport bar but has great beer and great bar food. Great location, tons of space, friendly staff.

Solid beer selection both in house and local.  Enjoyed our pub food and looking to go back for dinner.  In an area with few options, it's a real find...

Amazing selection of sour beers. A nice atmosphere with excellent lighting and brew house style seating. Come with friends!

Stopped in after work and service was great! Tired a beer on tap called Cherry Hound and it was great. My food came out super fast and was just to my liking. Wish I had more time to stay looked like a band was setting up to play. I'm so going have to bring my friends here.

Tried 6 or 7 different beers. They are heavy on the sours which is fine, but several tasted unfinished. We liked Mr pitz.  Didn't try the food.
Such a shame. Cool venue, but mediocre flavored food and poor service/attitude of waiters. They could use some people that are a lot more personable
Loved the beer quality and variety. Several good veggie options on the menu, as well. Located in a cool spot in a renovated warehouse just north of downtown Philly.
Great beer, food and staff

My husband and I stopped past on a Saturday afternoon.  We were able to get a seat at the bar.  We ate and had a couple of beers.  Food was surprisingly good for a brewery.  Beer was excellent as well.  No complaints.

Awesome atmosphere and well lit since one entire wall is windows on the street side. Interesting beers and a solid food menu. Not crowded on a Saturday afternoon with plenty of bar and communal table space. Well i formed friendly staff.
Great bar food and a good selection of house brewed beers. Also have some out of house beers. The location is whatever but inside has nice decore.

This place is awesome for after work drinks, and casual eats with friends and family. The expansive list of in house drafts are all good in their own way, and the food is fantastic. Wish there was a larger selection of cheap bar food, but what is on the menu is delicious.
Awesome.

Great menu and atmosphere. I got both flavors of their chicken wings and was not overly impressed but they have a great beer selection. Their sour beers are fantastic.
Nice find, great beers, deserves more business.

Good beer, good good, nice people. Awesome location. They're going to be brawling with my friends from Yards in a little while.

Haven't been there but they have a keg at Mad mex. Good stuff. Been my goto while on tap here.

Big fan!  This is a great addition to the neighborhood.  Lots of varieties of beer to please all palates.  Food is good - menu was not big initially but that has changed.  Not hungry for a full meal, DO NOT pass on the pretzel - it's awesomely good!
